					<h2>Blue whales are the stars this week</h2>
					<p><img src="/images/blue-fluke.jpg" alt="Blue Whales while Whale Watching in Monterey Bay California with Stagnaro Charters"></p>
					<p>We've had amazing BLUE WHALES in big numbers on all trips this week!</p>
					<p><em>Wednesday, May 25</em> — Surrounded by BLUE WHALE spouts today- showing flukes today near Santa Cruz! Also, humpback whales in the bay! A few were tail-throwing and pec-slapping at the surface.</p>
					<p><em>Sunday, May 22</em> –Many blue whales again. Wonderful sightings – they are quite actively diving to feed in the deep waters, giving as great flukes. Humpback whales also active in the bay.</p>
					<p><em>Saturday, May 21</em> — 15 Blue Whales!! Diving; great looks at flukes. Plus otters, sea lions, migrating birds and dolphins!</p>
					<p><img src="/images/blue2.jpg" alt="Blue Whales while Whale Watching in Monterey Bay California with Stagnaro Charters"></p>
					<p class="credit">Blue whale tail Monterey Bay, with Santa Cruz Whale Watching, Photo: Michael Nelson</p>
					<p><img src="/images/5-23-16-768.jpg" alt="Sightings while Whale Watching in Monterey Bay California with Stagnaro Charters"></p>
					<p><img src="/images/5-23-16-2.jpg" alt="Sightings while Whale Watching in Monterey Bay California with Stagnaro Charters"></p>
					<p><img src="/images/5-23-16-4.jpg" alt="Sightings while Whale Watching in Monterey Bay California with Stagnaro Charters"></p>
					<p>Earlier in May we had a week with large groups of active Orcas, hunting in Monterey Bay. It is amazing to see these fantastic "killer whales" out in nature.</p>
